  "texts": [
    "However, there is little emphasis on the important regions with their features, and the redundant regions cause classification problems.",
    "Researchers have utilized various feature improvement techniques to overcome this issue, including identifying more effective means of feature fusion [17], selecting more efficient feature maps [25], and incorporating attention processes into CNN [26].Recent developments in image classification for remote sensing applications have witnessed a rise in innovative strategies to cope with the challenges posed by complex spatial patterns and diverse semantic content [27,28].",
    "One notable avenue of exploration involves the integration of graph convolutional networks (GCNs) to enhance contextual modeling.",
    "GCNs leverage graph structures to capture relationships between pixels, thereby providing a more holistic understanding of scene elements and their interplay.",
    "This approach proves particularly valuable in scenarios where spatial dependencies are critical, contributing to improved accuracy in classifying remote sensing images with intricate object relationships.Authors in [29], propose dual Graph U-Nets for Hyperspectral imaging (HSI) classification (DGU-HSI) addresses limitations in conventional graph convolutional neural networks by integrating spatial and spectral graphs for feature extraction."
  ],
